# Styling Standards

## Tailwind CSS Usage
- Use Tailwind CSS 4 for all styling
- Prefer utility classes over custom CSS
- Use responsive prefixes (sm:, md:, lg:, xl:) for breakpoints
- Follow mobile-first responsive design approach

## CSS Organization
- Global styles in [src/app/globals.css](mdc:src/app/globals.css)
- Component-specific styles using Tailwind classes
- Use CSS custom properties for theme values
- Avoid inline styles unless absolutely necessary

## Design System
- Use consistent spacing scale (4, 8, 16, 24, 32, 48, 64)
- Maintain consistent color palette
- Use semantic color names (primary, secondary, accent)
- Follow accessibility guidelines for contrast ratios

## Component Styling
- Create reusable component variants
- Use conditional classes for dynamic styling
- Leverage Tailwind's component extraction
- Keep styling close to component logic

## Responsive Design
- Mobile-first approach
- Use container queries when appropriate
- Test on multiple screen sizes
- Ensure touch-friendly interactions on mobile
